{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/early-progress/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"880 Project Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f9f54aed-debc-5b0f-b7ed-2ad2afc20b7a","excerpt":"This post is dated as April 1, 2023 merely to make it earlier than actual updates. I am using Unity 2021.3.20f1, as it is the most recent LTS build. I preferâ€¦","html":"<p><em>This post is dated as April 1, 2023 merely to make it earlier than actual updates.</em></p>\n<p>I am using Unity 2021.3.20f1, as it is the most recent LTS build. I prefer LTS builds of products when creating content with a purpose as LTS builds seem to offer some stability and fewer changes.</p>\n<h2>Level Design</h2>\n<p>Starting out, one of the first efforts was to learn to create a maze in Unity to help with designing the level. In an early build I worked through a tutorial for generating a random maze, which looked nice. While the maze had a nice appearance, it would make the objectives of the game overly complicated as the level is randomly generated at the start of each run of the game.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/e4611/random-maze-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.67088607594937%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Random Maze Generator 1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/f058b/random-maze-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/c26ae/random-maze-1.png 158w,\n/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/6bdcf/random-maze-1.png 315w,\n/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/f058b/random-maze-1.png 630w,\n/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/40601/random-maze-1.png 945w,\n/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/78612/random-maze-1.png 1260w,\n/static/9515d267a05d5d212e07b0ab65340b09/e4611/random-maze-1.png 1298w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nRandom Maze Generator 1</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/e4611/random-maze-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.67088607594937%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Random Maze Generator 2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/f058b/random-maze-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/c26ae/random-maze-2.png 158w,\n/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/6bdcf/random-maze-2.png 315w,\n/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/f058b/random-maze-2.png 630w,\n/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/40601/random-maze-2.png 945w,\n/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/78612/random-maze-2.png 1260w,\n/static/928af017af30834cad0a40d1ba7eaac4/e4611/random-maze-2.png 1298w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nRandom Maze Generator 2</p>\n<p>I then took the shape creation methods that I learned while working on the maze to construct a level. While this technically worked, managing the sizes and alignment of the shapes (which would be the walls, floors, etc.) was difficult. I wanted to find a way to set precise sizes. Around this time I also put some effort into learning to work with doors, but decided to come back to it after I had the core level structure in place.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/18266332bb3d8e4bd3853b93f75b6ad3/78274/grid-alignment.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 87.9746835443038%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Grid Alignment\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/18266332bb3d8e4bd3853b93f75b6ad3/f058b/grid-alignment.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/18266332bb3d8e4bd3853b93f75b6ad3/c26ae/grid-alignment.png 158w,\n/static/18266332bb3d8e4bd3853b93f75b6ad3/6bdcf/grid-alignment.png 315w,\n/static/18266332bb3d8e4bd3853b93f75b6ad3/f058b/grid-alignment.png 630w,\n/static/18266332bb3d8e4bd3853b93f75b6ad3/78274/grid-alignment.png 644w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nGrid Alignment</p>\n<p>Searching for methods of precisely controlling the sizes of my shapes, I encountered mention of the ProBuilder feature in many of the forums that I visited. Most of the post were older, and associated with early versions of Unity. THe procedures for getting ProBuilder added were no longer accurate. After some time I learned the procedure for getting ProBuilder added to my Unity (2021.3.20f1) environment.</p>\n<p>Two of the resources that helped me to get started were Unity's learn.unity.com site and a tutorial by Brackeys, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtzIXCKr8Wo\">MAKING YOUR FIRST LEVEL in Unity with ProBuilder!</a>.</p>\n<p>The level is loosely based on the layout of Lutherville Physicians, which is a semi-symmetrical medical hub for Mercy Hospital in Baltimore. Due to the semi-symmetrical layout, I built half of the level and mirrored the other half once the main structure was completed.</p>\n<h2>Player Controller</h2>\n<p>The next big hurdle was to add a player.</p>\n<p><em>The sleep has come for me; I'll add more info soon.</em></p>\n<h2>Assets</h2>\n<p>I knew of the Unity Asset Store due to my work as a lab manager who supports University of Baltimore's game design program. Aside from needing to preload a package on all systems some years ago, this was my first interaction with the asset store. I was suprised by the range of content that was freely available, as well as the cost of premium content.</p>\n<p>Latest WebGL Build: <a href=\"https://play.unity.com/mg/other/webgl-6ej\">https://play.unity.com/mg/other/webgl-6ej</a></p>\n<p>Advisor: <a href=\"https://www.towson.edu/fcsm/departments/computerinfosci/facultystaff/ztang.html\">Dr. Ziying Tang</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Early Progress","date":"April 01, 2023","description":"Some documentation of progress that was made before the start of this blog."}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/project-overview/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Project Overview"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"f9f54aed-debc-5b0f-b7ed-2ad2afc20b7a","previousPostId":null,"nextPostId":"0b418d65-bf57-501e-aed2-a3e5debbcc2a"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","3257411868"],"slicesMap":{}}